The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 January is 30,133 (3,487.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 January, there were 4,975 new confirmed cases (575.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 January, there were 6,508 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (1,533 fewer cases).
